<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Minister Breaks Off Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bulgarian Minister Breaks Off Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404085494 Sofia BTA in English 0627 GMT 14 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BTA correspondent Nikolay Koev] </F>
  [Text] Skopje, April 14 (BTA) -- The two-day official visit 
of Bulgarian Minister of Science and Education Marko Todorov to 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
was broken off yesterday. 
  Having conferred with his Macedonian counterparts Selmani 
and 
Bajaldziev on April 12, at the end of his visit Todorov was to 
sign a protocol on cooperation between the similar ministries of 
the two countries. The document, coordinated in advance with 
Macedonian experts in Sofia, said that the protocol was to be 
signed in the official languages in Bulgaria and Macedonia. 
  Yesterday the Macedonian side demanded that this established 
wording in bilateral practice and documentation be substituted 
for [as received] "the Macedonian and Bulgarian languages." The 
Bulgarian side refused to sign the document which marked the end 
of the visit which also envisaged a meeting with Macedonian 
Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

