<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDP Holds Congress `Despite Police Threats' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDP Holds Congress `Despite Police Threats' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304073194 Tirana ATA in English 1035 GMT 11 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1304073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 11 (ATA) -- Great Macedonian [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] police forces 
refused entry on April 10 in the Palace of Culture in Tetove 
where the congress of the branch of the Democratic Prosperity 
Party [PDP] in this city would be held, Albanian television 
reported on April 10. Despite police threats, participants of 
the congress, led by the DPP chairman, Arber Xhaferri and Deputy 
Chairman Mendu Thaci, held the congress in the residence of 
this party in Tetove. 
  Referring to reports from Tetove, Albanian television said 
that participants in the congress declared that they will not 
allow any compromise detrimental to the just resolution of the 
question of the Albanians in the Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia. 

</TEXT>

