<H3> <TI>   Greek Embassy Given 10 Days To Reduce Staff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Embassy Given 10 Days To Reduce Staff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304193794 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1304193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 13 April 1994 Khristodhoulos Tsalikis, Greek 
ambassador in Tirana, was summoned to the Foreign Ministry and 
was handed a note saying that owing to the lack of an agreement 
on the necessary personnel of the diplomatic staff of the 
Republic of Albania in Athens and the Republic of Greece in 
Tirana, the Albanian side considers that these staffs should 
each be reduced to six diplomats. 
  The Embassy of the Greek Republic in Tirana should take the 
necessary measures to send home, within 10 days, all diplomatic 
staff in excess of this number. 

</TEXT>

