<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Intensified Economic Cooperation With </F>
Hungary"] 
  [Text] A delegation of the Macedonian Foreign Ministry, 
led by Under Secretary Dmitar Belcev, held talks in Budapest on 
coordinating the Agreement on Economic and Trade Cooperation 
between Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- 
FYROM] and Hungary. The agreement specifies ways to intensify 
and develop economic cooperation, especially in the field of 
metallurgy, chemical industry, and the agriculture. Belcev 
informed in detail of the damages caused by the Greek embargo 
against Macedonia. 

