<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Difficulties of Coexistence in Vojvodina Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Difficulties of Coexistence in Vojvodina Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304193994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1700 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The coexistence of Hungarians and Serbs in Vojvodina 
is growing more difficult, since nationalism has further 
increased. This is what Andras Agoston, chairman of the 
Democratic Community of Vojvodina Hungarians, told Hungarian 
Socialist Party Chairman Gyula Horn. Andras Agoston expressed 
hope that in the future a clear and verifiable system will be 
established in the mother country to support the organizations 
of Hungarians beyond the borders. 
  Gyula Horn considered it important that the Hungarian 
political forces, independent of their party political 
affiliation and ideology, should be united in support of the 
Vojvodina Hungarians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

