<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Describes Talks With Iraq on Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Describes Talks With Iraq on Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304132594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1000 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1304132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Marcel Dinu, secretary of the Romanian Foreign 
Affairs Ministry, returned to Bucharest today together with the 
four Romanian citizens who had been pardoned and freed from 
prison in Iraq following a request by Romanian President Ion 
Iliescu. 
  Talking to our correspondent at Otopeni International 
Airport, Dinu said that on that occasion he also held talks with 
Iraqi authorities regarding the payment of the debts owed by 
Iraq to Romania, which amount to $1.8 to 1.9 billion. The Iraqi 
party asserted that after the lifting of the [UN] embargo it 
will look for possible ways to pay its debts. 
  Talks were also held to establish contacts between Romanian 
and Iraqi economic companies, while observing the UN Security 
Council resolutions. 
  Dinu mentioned to our reporter that there are three other 
Romanian citizens held in Iraqi prisons, who were arrested for 
stealing. Diplomatic steps are being made to obtain the 
reduction of their prison terms, Dinu said, as Iraqi laws do not 
allow for the annulling of their punishment. 

</TEXT>

