<H3> <TI>   Government Withdraws AFP, CNN Accreditations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Withdraws AFP, CNN Accreditations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304184794 Paris AFP in English 1823 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1304184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, April 13 (AFP) -- The Yugoslav 
government officially withdrew press accreditations from AFP 
correspondents here Wednesday [13 April], accusing them of 
waging a "media war" against Belgrade. 
  The information ministry withdrew accreditations from bureau 
chief Nicolas Miletitch and three other journalists to cover 
events in Serbia and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM], but not for Serb-held areas of Croatia and 
Bosnia. 
  On Tuesday the ministry accused AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE and 
Cable News Network (CNN) of "waging a merciless media war 
against Yugoslavia, from its territory." [passage omitted] 
  The AFP journalists whose accreditation was withdrawn can 
continue to coordinate coverage of events in Macedonia and 
Albania. 

</TEXT>

