<H3> <TI>   Correspondents Expelled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Correspondents Expelled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204183094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1804 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 12 Apr -- The Federal Yugoslav Information 
Ministry said in a statement this evening that accreditations 
would be withdrawn from the French AFP news agency correspondent 
and the correspondent of the American CNN TV network. 
  The statement reads: 
  ``Federal Information Minister Slobodan Ignjatovic has 
decided to take legal measures against the correspondents who 
have been waging a fierce media war against Yugoslavia, and this 
on the territory of Yugoslavia. This practically means that 
accreditations will be withdrawn from the AFP and CNN 
correspondents and they will not be permitted to do any further 
work from tomorrow, 13 April. 
  "Acreditations will also be withdrawn in the next few days 
from other foreign media correspondents who have been demonizing 
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and the Serb people for 
months, and some of them for years," the statement says. 

</TEXT>

