<H3> <TI>   AFP `Strongly' Protests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AFP `Strongly' Protests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204204194 Paris AFP in English 1951 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1204204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, April 12 (AFP) -- The Yugoslav 
information ministry said Tuesday [12 April] it was withdrawing 
press accreditation from AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE [AFP] and Cable 
News Network (CNN), accusing them of waging a "media war" 
against Belgrade. 
  The exact reason for the move was not immediately clear. 
  AFP management strongly protested the measure, calling for 
the decision to be reversed. [passage omitted] 
  An AFP management statement said: "AFP has followed the 
ethical rules of the profession rigidly and in all areas, over 
the several decades it has been in Yugoslavia." 
  The cause of the Yugoslav action was not immediately clear. 
It came after NATO air raids on Bosnian Serb forces besieging 
the eastern Bosnian Moslem enclave of Gorazde. 
  CNN does not have a permanent bureau in Belgrade. 

</TEXT>

