<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin in Belgrade on `Surprise Visit' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin in Belgrade on `Surprise Visit' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304183594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1818 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 13 April (TANJUG) -- Vitaliy Churkin, 
the Russian president's special envoy, arrived from Pale in 
Belgrade late this afternoon, where he was received by Serbian 
President Slobodan Milosevic. 
  Their strictly confidential talks were held behind closed 
doors but there is no doubt that the main reason for Churkin's 
surprise visit to Belgrade is the newly created situation in 
Bosnia following NATO air strikes on Serb positions around 
Gorazde. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

