Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Initiative Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peace Initiative Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304184894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1824 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 13 Apr (TANJUG) -- Serbian President 
Slobodan Milosevic this evening again received Vitaliy Churkin, 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin's special envoy, who arrived in 
Belgrade following talks in Sarajevo and Pale. 
  As the Serbian president's office has announced, the talks 
focused on the current situation, while particular attention was 
paid to the initiative for reaching a general agreement on the 
cessation of all hostilities on the territory of former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The Serbian president stressed in talks that abandoning the 
practice of discriminating between the warring sides in former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina represents an unavoidable precondition for 
reaching a final peace. 

</TEXT>

