<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Soldier Hit by Sniper Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Soldier Hit by Sniper Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404101394 Paris AFP in English 1003 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1404101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 14 (AFP) -- Serb forces seized 17 UN 
peacekeepers Thursday guarding a weapons stockpile at Cifluk, 19 
kilometres (12 miles) northwest of Sarajevo, UN Protection Force 
spokesman Rob Annink said. 
  The peacekeepers -- 14 Canadian peacekeeping troops and 
three 
UN military observers of unspecified nationality -- were taken 
by the Serbs to a barracks at Ilijas, Annink said. 
  Cifluk lies just inside the heavy weapons exclusion zone 
around Sarajevo ordered by the United Nations in February. 
  A French UN soldier was wounded Thursday morning by Serb 
sniper fire, UN spokesman for Sarajevo Lieutenant-Colonel 
Richard Pernod said. 
  He said the soldier was hit while manning an anti-sniper 
post 
near Vrbanja bridge on the front line not far from central 
Sarajevo. He was rushed to hospital for surgery but the 
spokesman had no details on his condition. 
  Nineteen French UN troops have been killed so far in 
ex-Yugoslavia while more than 250 have been injured, the 
spokesman said. 
  The incidents came amid heightened tension in the capital 
and 
other points in Bosnia after NATO air strikes against Serb 
attackers besieging the eastern Moslem enclave of Gorazde, a 
UN-declared safe area. 
  Sarajevo was rocked Wednesday by two series of explosions 
that marred a two-month old ceasefire, as Bosnian Serb strongman 
said he had "cancelled" all accords with the United Nations 
after the air strikes, saying he could no longer trust the world 
body. 
  Earlier Wednesday, Radio Sarajevo said Serb forces continued 
an offensive against Gorazde, despite an announcement Wednesday 
by Russian envoy Valeriy Churkin that he had brokered a 
ceasefire around the enclave. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-8509 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu072_i_94005" </HT>


