<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attack Intensifies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attack Intensifies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404145794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1404145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Musovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] Continuing their fierce offensive on Gorazde, the 
chetniks have since morning been launching extremely heavy 
combined artillery and infantry attacks on (Borovo) from the 
direction of Ustipraca, and on the right bank of the Drina River 
from the direction of Cajnice. The aggressor has deployed very 
strong forces, reinforced with newly arrived units from the 
Uzice Corps, the Herzegovina Corps, and the Sarajevo-Mt. 
Romanija Corps, and special units from Nis, which are equipped 
with the most state-of-the-art weapons and the most lethal ones, 
too. 
  The information from these areas indicates that extremely 
heavy fighting is under way. The chetnik attacks on these 
defense lines are continuing. The aggressor is pounding every 
inch of these areas with mortars of the heaviest caliber. The 
fighters of the Eastern Bosnia Operative Group of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, the unrelenting defenders of Gorazde, 
are withholding all the attacks by these insane killers [word 
indistinct] to enter Gorazde as soon as possible. 
  There is total chaos in the clinic and the Gorazde war 
hospital. Screams, cries, and the wailing of children. Several 
people have been killed today by shells that have landed on the 
town. The exact number is still unknown, but the deaths of 
three children and two women have been confirmed. Dozens of 
civilians have also been wounded, three of them children and one 
woman very seriously. 
  The chetniks are shelling the surrounding villages, but we 
have no information about the casualties from these areas. 
During the day the aggressor has also intensified attacks on 
all the other defense lines. The chetniks are simultaneously 
reinforcing their forces, and concentrating them from the 
direction of Foca, (Medici), and the Praca River valley . 
  The general alarm has been in force in Gorazde since this 
morning owing to the shelling of the residential areas in the 
region. The Gorazde defenders are putting up strong resistance 
to the aggressor despite the inadequacy of their weapons. 

</TEXT>

