<H3> <TI>   Karadzic: U.S. Now `Warring Faction' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic: U.S. Now `Warring Faction' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304183094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1753 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 13 Apr (TANJUG) -- "We are ready for a 
peace process but we are not ready to accept as negotiators 
those who ordered the bombing of the Serb positions," Srpska 
republic president Radovan Karadzic said ahead of talks with 
David Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg, cochairmen of the 
conference on Yugoslavia. He stressed that the Serb side would 
choose who will be the mediators in peace negotiations. 
  "The European Union was completely pushed out of the 
resolution of the Bosnia-Herzegovina conflict after Washington 
launched its diplomatic initiative," Karadzic. He added that now 
"a new crisis has been created in which the United States can be 
proclaimed a warring faction." 
  "This may be the moment for the European Union to return to 
the political scene in search of solutions to the current 
conflicts in Bosnia," the Srpska republic president said. 

</TEXT>

