<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy To Visit Zagreb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy To Visit Zagreb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304200094 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy intends to arrive in Croatia 
tomorrow, (Aleksey Vedemkin), Zhirinovskiy's envoy, has told 
HINA. The Russian Embassy in Croatia is in no way involved in 
Zhirinovskiy's visit to Zagreb, a representative of the embassy 
has stated, adding that the embassy knows nothing about 
Zhirinovskiy's reasons for the visit or its schedule, and does 
not know who invited him. 
  The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Croatia has 
announced 
that no official body has invited Zhirinovskiy to Croatia. 
Given that his possible visit is of a private nature, the 
Croatian state authorities will proceed in accordance with legal 
regulations determining the conditions of entry for foreign 
nationals and their stay in the Republic of Croatia. 

</TEXT>

