<H3> <TI>   Army To Buy Only Czech-Made Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army To Buy Only Czech-Made Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504100594 Prague CTK in English 2116 GMT 14 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1504100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 14 (CTK) -- In future, the Czech Army 
will only be purchasing weapons and equipment from Czech 
suppliers, NOVA Television said today, citing deputy Defense 
Minister Miroslav Kalousek. 
  Kalousek said NOVA said [as received] that the army is 
considering placing a commission for a modernized version of the 
T- 72 tank with the Czech weapons producers. 
  Kalousek was taking part in a meeting in Jihlava, South 
Moravia, of representatives of Czech weapon factories, the 
Defense and Interior ministries, and other producers which 
looked at the possibility of the Czech Army, police, and 
national security tapping the potential of Czech weapon 
companies. 
  The meeting followed a plenary meeting of the weapons 
consortium RDP Group. 
  The RDP Group Praha joint venture was founded last year to 
negotiate with the ministries and government. Forty 
shareholders participate in it. 

</TEXT>

