<H3> <TI>   Czech Automaker To Open Plant in Poznan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Automaker To Open Plant in Poznan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94CH0218A Prague PRAGUE POST in English 29 Mar 94 p 2--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94CH0218A </F>
<F P=104>  Prague PRAGUE POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by James Hider: "Skoda To Produce Cars in Poland"] </F>
  [Text] The Mlada Boleslav automaker Skoda announced March 
18 that it will produce automobiles abroad for the first time in 
its history. It intends to open a plant in the Polish city of 
Poznan that will turn out an estimated 5,000 cars this year, 
with a capacity for expansion in the future. Ludvik Kalma, 
director of the factory in Mlada Boleslav, explained that this 
is the only way to avoid restrictive tariffs on exporting Czech 
cars to Poland. Skoda has negotiated unsuccessfully with Polish 
officials to reduce these duties, which could increase car 
prices by as much as 41 percent. 

</TEXT>

