<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Update on Berov's Health Condition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Berov's Health Condition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404154094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1404154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After a prolonged medical consultation, it was 
announced at a news conference at the Council of Ministers that 
in the last three to four days an acute illness developed in 
Professor Berov's liver. There are tendencies toward 
improvement in the clinical and laboratory indices. 
  The patient has slight hepatitis but with a tendency to heal 
within a brief period of time. There are two versions about the 
basic cause: Either a mechanical clogging of the gall bladder 
vessels, which occurred and passed rapidly, or a light form of 
an acute hepatitis virus. This was announced by 
gastroenterologist Professor Konstantin Chernev. A specific 
blood test of the patient will be carried out abroad. The result 
will be known within several days. 

</TEXT>

