<H3> <TI>   NATO Aircraft Overfly Serb Positions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO Aircraft Overfly Serb Positions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404182794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1733 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Excerpt] Cajnice, April 14 (TANJUG)--NATO aircraft flew 
over Bosnian Serb positions between Gorazde and Cajnice in 
eastern Bosnia-Herzegovina at 16:00 hours local time on 
Thursday, TANJUG has learned from Bosnian Serb Army (VRS) 
sources. 
  According to the same sources, there have be no reports 
about 
whether the aircraft undertook combat action in the area of the 
two towns which are close to the border with the Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia. 
  U.S. NATO aircraft on Sunday and Monday raided Bosnian Serb 
positions around Gorazde, a U.N.-protected "safe area" which 
should have been demilitarized last spring. Not only that 
Gorazde has not been demilitarized, but it was used to mass over 
10,000 Muslim troops and launch a strong offensive on Bosnian 
Serb territory in late March. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

