<H3> <TI>   Muslim `Operation' North of Sarajevo Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim `Operation' North of Sarajevo Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504105794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0948 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sarajevo, 15 Apr (TANJUG) -- Heavy fighting has 
been going on for two days on the several-dozen-km-long front 
line in the northern part of the Sarajevo battlefield. 
  According to Serb intelligence sources, Muslim forces have 
engaged about 15,000 soldiers of the 7th, 2d, and 3d Corps, as 
well as parts of the Sarajevo Corps, in their attacks from the 
direction of Kakanj and Vares, Mt. Zvijezda, and Olovo. 
  According to an assessment by Serb military sources, the 
objective of the comprehensive Muslim operation is to capture 
the Nisici plateau, to take control of the Nisici-Srednje and 
Olovo-Sarajevo roads, and to break through the lines in Ilijas 
and Vogosca, which would enable them to link their forces from 
central Bosnia with those from Sarajevo. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

