<H3> <TI>   Delic Tells Silajdzic of Need To Continue War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delic Tells Silajdzic of Need To Continue War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404170994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1404170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of the Day of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army, Army General Rasim Delic, supreme commander of the General 
Staff, has sent Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister a note of 
congratulations, which, among other things, says: 
  We are convinced that this year's marking of the Day of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army -- when we recall all the difficulties 
and casualties but also the results we have achieved -- will be 
a great motivation to all of us to continue the war of 
liberation in an even more organized and effective way, with 
dignity and courage to persist in the establishment of a just 
peace. 
  In that respect, we are aware of the moral obligation we 
have 
toward the casualties among the population, the killed fighters, 
our sehids [Muslim fighters killed in battle], our invalids, and 
[word indistinct]. 
  I would like to use this opportunity to express my 
satisfaction and gratitude to you -- your personal stature and 
results, particularly in the diplomatic sense -- for being a 
significant force in preserving and strengthening the moral and 
combat effectiveness of the units and commands of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 
  This is said in the note of congratulations from Army 
General 
Rasim Delic to Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic on the occasion of 
15 April, the day of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 

</TEXT>

