<H3> <TI>   Agreements Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreements Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504121094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] High-ranking Croat and Muslim political 
representatives agreed yesterday in Sarajevo on the release of 
prisoners and on a number of political issues related to the 
functioning of the Bosnia-Herzegovina federation, the 
Herzeg-Bosna delegation said on their return from Sarajevo. 
Zdenko Vranjes reports from Mostar: 
  [Vranjes] The negotiations in Sarajevo were held in a good 
atmosphere. It was agreed who can represent the Croat and 
Muslim people at the federation level until new elections are 
held. It was also agreed that legal preparations should 
commence to form a government of the federation. It has still 
not been agreed whether the person holding the post of president 
of the federation until the elections should be a Croat or a 
Bosniak, nor what nationality the deputy president and the prime 
minister should be. This decision is to be made by the 
constituent assembly, which is expected to hold a session at the 
end of this month. 
  Before that high-ranking representatives of the two peoples 
will meet again and discuss the remaining issues. 

</TEXT>

