<H3> <TI>   Muslims, Croats Sign Prisoner Exchange Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims, Croats Sign Prisoner Exchange Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504074194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0700 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504074194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An agreement on the release of prisoners from 
prisons under the control of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and the 
Croat Defense Council has been signed. 
  Those charged with or sentenced for the most serious 
criminal 
offenses will not be released if the signatories show the Red 
Cross by Sunday that charges have been pressed or sentences 
passed. An international committee of experts is to be founded 
to interview those accused of the most serious criminal acts 
within 30 days and examine all evidence relevant to the criminal 
procedures. After that the committee will make decisions on the 
further detention of the accused. The agreement says that the 
Red Cross will determine the dynamics and mode of implementation 
of the prisoner release. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

