<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Manolic Refuses To Convene Assembly Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Manolic Refuses To Convene Assembly Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404211694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1404211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Josip Manolic, president of the Croatian Assembly's 
Chamber of Counties, has refused to convene a session of the 
Chamber in eight days' time, Chamber of Counties Secretary Anton 
Rajcevac told journalists today. 
  At the proposal of some Croatian Democratic Union deputies 
to 
convene a session, Manolic, referring to the standing orders, 
said he did not consider that the reasons to convene a session 
of the Chamber of Counties in eight days' time were justified 
and that he would convene it when he found it necessary for this 
assembly chamber to perform its constitutional obligations. 

</TEXT>

