<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Another Meeting Expected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Another Meeting Expected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404155494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1355 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1404155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kondrashov] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, 14 Apr -- Vitaliy Churkin, Russian 
Federation president's special envoy, again met Serb President 
Slobodan Milosevic today. They discussed the situation in 
Bosnia and Russia's new proposals on overcoming the current 
Bosnian crisis caused by NATO airstrikes against Bosnian 
positions near Gorazde. 
  In a brief statement to the press after the meeting, the 
Russian deputy foreign minister refrained from revealing the 
content of these proposals. They relate to halting hostilities 
and restoring normal life in Bosnia, which is a prerequisite for 
a political solution to the Bosnian crisis, he said. 
  As an ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from well-informed 
sources, a joint meeting of the Serb president, Bosnian Serb 
leadership, and the Russian Federation president's special envoy 
can be expected in the near future to discuss Russia's new 
proposals and determine the Serb side's relevant position. 

</TEXT>

