<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Declaration on EU Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Adopts Declaration on EU Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404132494 Sofia BTA in English 1234 GMT 14 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 14 (BTA) -- The Bulgarian Government 
reiterates Bulgaria's hope to be granted full membership in the 
European Union [EU]. Bulgaria is ready to make the required 
representations as soon as the prerequisites for that have been 
created, says a declaration of the Council of Ministers adopted 
today. 
  The document states the resolution of the Bulgarian 
Government to do its best and accelerate this process, proceed 
with the reforms and create the necessary economic, legislative 
and other conditions for Bulgaria's full integration into the EU. 
  The government is ready to continue its political dialogue 
with the EU on foreign policy and security issues on both 
bilateral and multilateral bases. 
  The Council of Ministers suggests that the National Assembly 
consider the effective acts of the EU in the course of its 
legislative work in order to bring Bulgarian legislation in line 
with their standards. In their cooperation with the 
institutions of the EU member countries, the Bulgarian 
ministries and departments will be guided by the stipulations of 
this declaration. 
  The government will rely on the cooperation and support of 
the European Council, the European Commission and the EU 
countries in the implementation of its declaration, the document 
says in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

