<H3> <TI>   Colombian Foreign Minister Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colombian Foreign Minister Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With President Havel </H4>

<F P=102> AU1204183294 Prague CTK in English 1800 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 11 (CTK) -- Colombian Foreign 
Minister Nohemi Sanin Posada believes that Czech President 
Vaclav Havel, along with Pope John Paul II and former Soviet 
President Michail Gorbachev, are three people who have ended the 
process of the European totalitarianism, Havel's spokesman 
Ladislav Spacek told journalists after meeting between Posada 
and Havel today. 
  He said that Posada had voiced her admiration at the 
restoration of political and economic freedoms in the Czech 
Republic. 
  Havel and Posada agreed on the need to deepen cooperation 
between the Czech Republic and Columbia, especially in the 
economic, technical and scientific fields, Spacek said. 
  Havel acquainted Posada with the basic transformation 
principles of the Czech Republic and primarily with the 
privatization process. 
  Posada conveyed to Havel an invitation from Colombian 
President Cesar Gaviria Trujill to visit Columbia, Spacek said, 
adding that in his turn Havel invited the Colombian president to 
visit the Czech Republic. 

</TEXT>

