<H3> <TI>   Colombian Foreign Minister Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colombian Foreign Minister Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discusses Cooperation With Uhde </H4>

<F P=102> AU1204193594 Prague CTK in English 1813 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 12 (CTK) -- Colombian Foreign 
Minister Nohemi Sanin Posada, in a meeting with Czech Parliament 
Chairman Milan Uhde today, pointed to the as yet not-utilized 
possibilities for Czech-Colombian political, economic and 
cultural cooperation. 
  She described the current level of Czech-Colombian trade as 
a 
symbolic one, adding that the Czech and Colombian economies were 
fully compatible and were not competing each other in any 
branch. She said that the Czech Republic was capable of standing 
up to competition in Latin American area too. 
  "We have lost many opportunities and this should be 
stopped," 
she said, referring to Czech-Colombian political, economic and 
cultural cooperation. 
  Uhde said that the Czech Republic was capable of offering, 
under advantageous conditions, different kinds of technology to 
Columbia. He mentioned metro construction project in the 
Colombian town of Medelin, Posada's native town, adding that 
such an opportunity should be made use of. 
  Uhde described the Czech Republic as a reliable partner 
pointing to the political stability and its favorable economic 
development. He said that agreements on investment protection 
and on the prevention of double taxation and tax evasion would 
contribute to Czech-Colombian cooperation. 

</TEXT>

