<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Sends Note </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Sends Note </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1604200094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1635 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1604200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As has been reported, at about 1030 on 15 April, at 
Borshi Bay, Albanian coast guard forces detected and detained 
the Greek ship Aios Vasilios while it was sailing about 2 miles 
into Albanian territorial waters. An hour later a Greek warship 
approached the fishing ship apprehended by our forces. 
  The Albanian torpedo-boat notified the Greek warship of 
having entered Albanian waters and urged it to leave. The Greek 
warship left only after one hour. 
  Concerning this provocation by the Greek side, the Embassy 
of 
the Republic of Albania in Athens sent a note, in the name of 
the Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Albania, to the Foreign 
Ministry of Greece, asking the Greek Government to put an end to 
such actions, which impair the relations between the two 
countries and increase tension, by designating them as a 
continuation of previous Greek provocative actions and of the 
criminal event in Peshkepi in Gjirokaster village on 10 April 
1994. 
  The provocation in our territorial waters does not help but 
prevents the creation of the minimal necessary conditions and 
runs counter to the proposal by the Greek side itself to hold a 
meeting with the working groups of the Public Order Ministries 
of the two countries, the Albanian note ends. 

</TEXT>

