<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Videnov Protests to Zhelev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504171394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1504171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Press Center of the Bulgarian Socialist Party 
[BSP] has announced that Zhan Videnov, chairman of the BSP 
Supreme Council, who is a member of the Consultative Council on 
National Security, has sent a letter to President Zhelyu Zhelev 
in which he sharply protests the fact that the problem of the 
transshipment of the UN Protection Forces equipment has not been 
discussed in the Consultative Council of National Security. 
  The letter points out that the president has once again 
proven his intention to turn the council into a declarative 
organ or a curtain behind which machinations are conducted. 
  Similar actions cannot be described as a manifestation of 
concern with the country's security, the protest letter of Zhan 
Videnov to the president of the Republic points out. 

</TEXT>

