<H3> <TI>   Railroad Cars for UN Convoy Arrive `Unsealed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Railroad Cars for UN Convoy Arrive `Unsealed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804064894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0400 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1804064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the night of 17 April, an hour earlier than 
scheduled, the UN convoy with military equipment for the Blue 
Helmets in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] arrived from Romania at Ruse central train station. 
  The contradictory information about the transit route 
through 
Bulgarian territory and the hour at which the train will depart 
from Ruse prompted us to contact our reporter in Ruse, Natasha 
Dimitrova. 
  [Begin Dimitrova recording] The UN convoy, which arrived 
yesterday night at Ruse central train station, departed this 
morning at 0148. The reason for the delay in the departure was 
related to 25 wagons being unsealed and the accompanying 
documents missing. 
  According to the Bulgarian railroad authorities, receiving 
the convoy in this form from the Romanian colleagues was 
irregular. After a long dispute and clarifications, the two 
sides signed a protocol and prior to the departure the equipment 
was sealed with Romanian seals. No information about the 
precise amount of missing contents has been published. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

