<H3> <TI>   Journalists' Accreditation Not To Be Withdrawn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Journalists' Accreditation Not To Be Withdrawn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504175894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Unlike the Belgrade authorities, Montenegro will not 
withdraw accreditation from foreign journalists, said 
Information Minister Bozidar Jarebic. He added this action was 
mostly to the detriment of those who withdrew accreditation. 
There are many other ways of reaching agreements with 
journalists. That way Serbia finally showed that isolation was 
its permanent political choice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

